args: What say you to resting for a while\nin this town, Your Highness?

That's a good idea; everyone's dead on
their feet from fighting so many fiends.
Let's stay here for a while before we
head back to the castl—
Are you guys travelers? Get out of here\nbefore you get dragged into any trouble!
There's a foreign swordsman and a large\npack of thugs in that street over there,\nand they're not discussing the weather!
Don't be makin' us out to be\nthe bad guys here, friend.
This town's my territory, and folks what\ndon't pay their dues get a little lesson.
Forcibly taking money from the innocent\nat the point of a sword is the very\ndefinition of a ＂bad guy.＂
I will not stand by and allow such things.\nLeave this town at once.
Looks like we got one more lesson\nto deal out. Let him have it, boys!
How'd he jump twice the height\nof his own body?!
Who cares HOW high he can jump?!\nI'm gonna kill this fool!
Caught the blow, didja?! Guess I'll have to\ncut right through that sword'a yours! Hah!
Then I shall pour my chi into my sword\nin order to repel you. Haaah!
This ain't no time for bein' impressed!\nTake him out already!
You don't know when to give up.\nAnd yet, I fear even my chi has limits.\nHmm... What to do...?
Well, if it ain't Ku Hai!
So you are the foreign swordsman\nthat villager was talking about.
We've heard all about what's going on,\nand we want to help however we can.
I appreciate your aid. Let us fight!
Uh oh. Time for this bird to fly!
Bwa ha ha! The alleys in this town are\nlike a maze; you ain't never gonna catch\nthe boss-man now!
Dunno why yer boastin' about a boss\nwhat just left ya high'n dry.
What?! How'd ya catch up to me?\nWhere'd ya even come from?!
I ran along the rooftops.\nNo maze is challenging when\none can view it from above.
Now it is time to teach you a lesson for\nall the ill deeds you have committed.\nPrepare yourself, coward!
Oh, thank you so much! Those guys have\nreally been making our lives miserable.
Let's have a celebration in honor\nof our new town heroes!
Thank you, but I would prefer not to.\nI find such attention...uncomfortable.
To hell with that! No one's gonna have\nany fun if the star of the show ain't there.
Hmm... I suppose that would not do.\nVery well—I shall do what I can to\nenjoy the occasion.
By the way, what brought you\nto this town to begin with?
I happened by during my wanderings.
Huh? But as soon as you arrived,\nyou asked where the thugs were!
I'm guessing ya heard a rumor and came \nto help, yeah? Why not just say so?
Regardless of your reasons, that was\na truly impressive leap.
And I love the way ya tossed them punks\naround like ragdolls! You must have one\nfine set'a muscles, my man.

I did not use muscles in my techniques.
I used chi kung to give myself bursts of
strength, and to increase the potency of
my sword.
It is a technique in which one refines\nthe chi—or mana—in their body.
Chi kung is often used in martial arts;\nthere are a number of dojos in Peng Lai\nthat teach its usage.
I was taught both chi kung and the art\nof the sword at the dojo I attended.
So training at a dojo is what\nmade you so strong?
Your master must be quite proud to have\ntrained such a capable student.
By the way, you wouldn't consider\ncoming to our castle, would you?
You're a capable fighter with a strong\nsense of justice. You could be a great\nasset to us in our struggle.
We would love your help to\nbring peace to this world.
If you prefer to continue your journey\nalone, we would understand.
You often find yourselves making journeys\nafar to answer requests for aid, yes?
In that case, I will join you. I actually\nWAS beginning to tire of traveling alone.
Right then! Now that we got ourselves\na new ally, it's time to party!

(As requests come to the prince from all
across the land, staying with him may be
a more efficient way to achieve my goal.
Plus, I wager rumors gather easily there.)
